Real Madrid manager, Zinedine Zidane, has released his side’s squad to face Galatasaray in today’s Champions League fixture at Santiago Bernabeu. Zidane announced a 19-man list to tackle the Turkish giants in a post on the club’s official Twitter page. Real Madrid head to the game after a 0-0 draw with Real Betis in the La Liga encounter last weekend. Below is the squad prepared against Galatasaray: Courtois, Areola, Altube, Carvajal, Militao, Sergio Ramos, Varane, Marcelo, Mendy, Kroos, Modric, Casemiro, Valverde, Isco, Hazard, Benzema, Jovic, Vinicius, Rodrygo. The kick-off time for the match is 9pm. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.